This paper proposes a new framework for enabling aggressive voltage underscaling of DNN accelerators without compromising classification accuracy even in the presence of high timing error rates. The paper focuses on energy efficiency of DNN accelerators and uses state-of-the-art speech and image recognition benchmarks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of timing errors on classification accuracy, which suggests the sub-category cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper proposes a new framework, which may fall under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
